        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I have a question.</P><P>What would be more effective for a necromancer?</P><P>Mana Stone - Mod-Rod - Life Tap/Arch Lich combo</P><P>Mana Stone: DANGEROUS Awesome for mana-hp convert but it only works in some zones when you have NO AGGRO and no longer drops making prices outragous for this one item.</P><P>Mod-Rod: HIGH CAUTION Great for mana-hp convert when you have NO AGGRO but you need to have lots of space in your inventory and a Mage to summon you plenty of them. Might cost you more in the long run.</P><P>Life Tap/Arch Lich combo: MED CAUTION This is great for downtime but when you need hp, you make AGGRO on a mob and that might be all you need to get yourself between a rock and a dead place. Furthermore as time proggresses, you eventually run out of fuel to keep going. That is unless a Necromancer is a perpetual death machine.</P><P>So what would you use and what DO you use while on a RAID, EXP GRIND, DOWNTIME????</P><P>I would perfer Mod-Rod; Life Tap/Arch Lich combo; Mana Stone in that order.</P><P>This is a question that I thought of while thinking of how to make us more like the Terminator Necronator. I hope that this helps you necros out there become more effective while making you a more superior necromancer.</P><P>EDIT: Changed Title of post from Necromancers... to what it is now.</P><P>Always thinking ...(processing)...<BR>Velous</P><P>They say dead people speak; but I say, Lets make them SCREAM!!</P><P>"I make dead people."</P><P>Edited by - Velous on 07/21/2002  02:19:33</font></td>

