        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well, biggest problem with Manastone is the zones it is viable in. Old world, non-planar zones only. What does that leave? The Hole. SolB. Lower Guk. If you are talking about a level 60 necro, those zones do not offer much any longer. Make breaking Djarn a bit easier maybe, or help your farming in Lower Guk possibly, but that seems to be the extent of it. Mana Robe is an alternative, but it has a longer casting time (3 seconds I believe, but do not quote me). I would imagine you could set up a shammy like canni-dance thing with it, but after playing a shammy, I can personally atest to the fact that it is a royal pain in the ass, and gets old pretty quick.</P><P>I know of a couple necros who like their toys, and have a Mana Robe, but I cannot ever remember seeing them actually use it ever.</P><P>With the mod-rods, it becomes a question of availability. Solo, normal grouping, smaller raids, a necro will never see a rod. Larger events, the rods go to clerics, then to wizzies, and if there are any left, a necro might get one here or there.</P><P>Personally, I go for a solid god-rod when the oportunity arises. It is a nice little kick of mana in those long fights. Would I spend money on a Mana Robe, or a Mana Stone as a necro? Probably not.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
