        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=51049&amp;TOPIC_ID=6229&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=More+Efficent+Necromancers%2E%2E%2E&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well, it would not really be due to its cast time. The cast time is 3.0 seconds. At the end of a tick, EQ does a single check to see if you are sitting, if you are, you get the mediation amount that tick. The thing is, you can be doing anything else for the rest of the round, and as long as you sit before the tick is up, you get the mana from meditation. Like what shammies do. Sit. Stand, cast canni. Sit, get the meditation mana. Stand, cast canni. Sit, get the meditation mana. Lather, rinse, repeat. So, techically, as long as you timed it right, you could constantly use the Mana Robe, while in Arch Lich form and still get the full mana benifit of meditation.</P><P>The thing that complicates this is the crappy ratio of a Mana Robe. 3HP for 1Mana. When you crunch the numbers on the mana it then takes to vex/deflux/TON that HP back, you are falling into the negative I believe. </P><P>It is the ratio that would kill a necro in the long run. The Mana Robe is mainly for wizzies with their epic. The right click takes off HP from a damage skin first, and since a wizzie's epic is a mana-free damage skin, they can click on their Mana Robe without losing HP.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
