        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=AIM&amp;AIM=bronstahd&amp;M_NAME=Karae')"><img src="icon_aim.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Send Karae an instant message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=51261&amp;TOPIC_ID=6229&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=More+Efficent+Necromancers%2E%2E%2E&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Uh I dunno about you but I've been in Lich 100% of the time since Kunark.</P><P>Manastone is a shitty ratio compared to Lich. Any necro with one of these is retarded.</P><P>Mod Rod 2 is unlimited damage. You get 2.5 ToN per Mod Rod 2 and lose zero health. Problem with Mod Rods is that you're dependent upon a mage.</P><P>As to the Mana Robe: yes, Arch Lich + medding is better than the Mana Robe alone. However, Arch Lich + Mana Robe is better than Arch Lich + medding. 75 Mana/tick vs 62. However, if you're going to be responsible for keeping yourself healed it is probably less effecient in the long run. You'll be losing an extra 120 hp every six seconds. 720 HP every 36 seconds (Which is one Touch of Night) so you'll be spending an additional 405 mana every 36 seconds, 6 ticks. 40 x 6 = 240. So overall you'll be down 165 mana from where you would be if you just sat with Arch Lich running. Albeit 720 damage ahead. Personally I think you'd lose damage in the long run. </P><P>Now, if you have a right click rune... Say, for example, Shield of Auras (this is likely the most common). That's a 300 damage rune. So we'll recast every second robe click, every six seconds, essentially. Shield is a 7 second cast. So we're at an additional mana gain of 40 every 13 seconds. Medding would give 54 mana over that period. Obviously medding is more effecient. However, the Mana Robe would be great to have in situations where you can't med; and believe me there are a lot. ;)</P><P>Personally I no longer have a Mana Robe. I have no desire to spend my time clicking a robe and reruning myself. I'll be content with Arch Lich and AoB. Oh and sooner or later a Talisman of Vah Kerrath. :) /rude DKP guildleader *cough*</P><P>Hope this clears the Mana Robe up for some.</P><P>Karae Qracfynd<BR>Fires of Heaven</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=183135" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=183135</a></P><P>Edited by - Karae on 07/22/2002  