         From all the cautions you put in your post Velous, you sound like a one of the very cautious Necromancers that only uses Clarity and KEI.</P><P>Necromancers are most efficient when they are below 100% health.  Our whole lives are spent tapping and liching.  That is our bread and butter.  Touch of Night is a 780 point (don't remember the exact number) direct damage AND heal.  If you aren't damaged, that extra healing portion is wasted.  Use it and love it.</P><P>Mana Stone, limited use and whimpy.</P><P>Mod-Rod, the only use I've found for them is extreme emergency group raid situations and raid whipeout recovery combo with Holgresh Elder Beads.</P><P>Arch-Lich is the best and only way for a well played necromancer to go as their standard.  In a raid situation, you'll have some form of Regrow, so the HP loss is minimal.  When I'm soloing, I always use Arch-Lich, damn the results.  I haven't died from a Lich spell since I was level 24.</P><P></P><P><center><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95266" target="_blank">Kuotat Smith</a><BR>Baroness <s>Warlock</s> Witch<BR>Mithaniel Marr </center><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
